{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place a pitcher onto mixing bowl lid, weigh in olive oil and set pitcher aside.","Place pecans into mixing bowl, place simmering basket instead of measuring cup onto mixing bowl lid and toast <b>5 min\/250°F\/\/speed 0.5<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place shallots, water, vinegar, lemon, mustard, salt and pepper into mixing bowl and mix <b>1 min\/speed 4<b>, while pouring reserved oil onto mixing bowl lid, letting it drizzle around measuring cup in a thin stream onto rotating blades to create an emulsion. Transfer dressing back into pitcher.","Place 12 oz cabbage into mixing bowl and chop <b>4 sec\/\/speed 5<b>. Transfer to a large bowl and set aside. Place remaining 12 oz cabbage into mixing bowl and chop <b>4 sec\/\/speed 5<b>. Transfer to bowl with reserved chopped cabbage, add watercress and reserved dressing, to taste, and toss through to combine.","Transfer to a serving platter and garnish with reserved toasted pecans. Serve immediately."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["2 oz olive oil","2 oz chopped pecans","½ oz shallots, cut into pieces","1 tbsp water","1 tbsp apple cider vinegar","1 tbsp freshly squeezed lemon juice (approx. ½ lemon, juiced)","1 tsp whole grain mustard","¼ tsp salt","&frac18; tsp ground black pepper","24 oz purple cabbage, cored, cut into pieces","2 oz watercress leaves, stems trimmed"]}],"id":"r315611","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-DzwibiRdARo\/XZMvTWEwndI\/AAAAAAAAaQI\/zMHHhq2HDnYzvzXfZyJFb2_Ww8wXcoQbwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_cm53KT_SZ783uAsc.png","title":"Purple Cabbage with Pecan Salad","publishedAt":"2018-03-09T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"3 g","fat":"8 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"11 g","calories":"502 kJ \/ 120 kcal"},"usefulItems":"serving platter, pitcher, large bowl","hintsAndTricks":["Replace watercress with baby arugula."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","15m","6 portions"]}